  <summary>6/22/1988--Introduced.
Amends part A (Aid to Families with Dependent Children) (AFDC) of title IV of the Social Security Act to require States to institute measures, in accordance with regulations to be issued by the Secretary of Health and Human Services within six months of this Act's enactment, to detect fraudulent AFDC applications before an applicant is determined to be eligible for such assistance.</summary>
